-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131198704.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/3500-year-old-mycenaean-woman-buried-with-swords-finally-gets-a-face-and-its-rewriting-ancient-history/articleshow/131198704.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/3500-year-old-mycenaean-woman-buried-with-swords-finally-gets-a-face-and-its-rewriting-ancient-history/articleshow/131198704.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-19T17:30:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131198716,imgsize-30660.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Steve Jobs’ Career Advice: Why his ‘connect the dots’ quote still guides work; small bets beat big plans]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131166754.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Steve Jobs' famous advice, 'You can't connect the dots looking forward; you can only connect them looking backwards,' offers a practical guide for navigating career uncertainty.  Instead of demanding clarity, finding meaning emerges from experiences.  This approach encourages exploration and 'small bets' over meticulous planning, fostering creativity and adaptability in today's dynamic job market.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/steve-jobs-said-you-cant-connect-the-dots-looking-forward-and-that-may-be-the-advice-ambitious-people-need-most/articleshow/131166754.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/steve-jobs-said-you-cant-connect-the-dots-looking-forward-and-that-may-be-the-advice-ambitious-people-need-most/articleshow/131166754.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-19T16:25:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131168462,imgsize-24540.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Iran used Romanian proxies to attack London-based Iranian journalist, UK court hears]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131201363.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/iranian-journalist-stabbed-in-london-by-tehran-linked-romanian-nationals-uk-court-hears/articleshow/131201363.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/iranian-journalist-stabbed-in-london-by-tehran-linked-romanian-nationals-uk-court-hears/articleshow/131201363.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-19T18:10:33+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131201436,imgsize-112294.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Why Reed Hastings' Netflix culture memo says working harder can quietly hurt your company]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131166750.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Netflix's famed cultural memo champions results over mere effort, challenging traditional workplaces that reward busyness. It advocates for 'talent density' and autonomy, urging managers to assess tasks by their impact rather than time spent. This approach, though sometimes uncomfortable, remains relevant for boosting genuine productivity by focusing on tangible achievements.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/why-reed-hastings-netflix-culture-memo-says-working-harder-can-quietly-hurt-your-company/articleshow/131166750.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/why-reed-hastings-netflix-culture-memo-says-working-harder-can-quietly-hurt-your-company/articleshow/131166750.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-19T16:10:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131176460,imgsize-60416.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Earth healers: Couple planted 2 million trees and brought an entire forest back to life]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131195078.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/earth-healers-couple-planted-2-million-trees-and-brought-an-entire-forest-back-to-life/articleshow/131195078.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/earth-healers-couple-planted-2-million-trees-and-brought-an-entire-forest-back-to-life/articleshow/131195078.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-19T14:07:49+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131195278,imgsize-1060521.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Jerash Mass Grave mystery: The 6th-century plague that erased an entire city in days]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131195431.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/jerash-mass-grave-mystery-the-6th-century-plague-that-erased-an-entire-city-in-days/articleshow/131195431.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/jerash-mass-grave-mystery-the-6th-century-plague-that-erased-an-entire-city-in-days/articleshow/131195431.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-19T15:00:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131195673,imgsize-65050.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists have created a steel sphere device that could help buildings survive earthquakes without electricity]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131196354.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-create-a-steel-sphere-device-that-could-help-buildings-survive-earthquakes-without-electricity/articleshow/131196354.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-create-a-steel-sphere-device-that-could-help-buildings-survive-earthquakes-without-electricity/articleshow/131196354.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-19T15:30:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131196501,imgsize-1383756.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[UAE to launch 16 new Indian passport and visa centres as Alhind takes over consular services]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131195661.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Over four million Indians in the UAE will experience a significant overhaul in passport and visa services starting July 1, 2026. Kerala-based Alhind Group has secured a major contract, launching 16 new service centers across the Emirates. This move aims to make services more affordable and accessible, replacing BLS International after a decade.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/uae-to-launch-16-new-indian-passport-and-visa-centres-as-alhind-takes-over-consular-services/articleshow/131195661.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/uae-to-launch-16-new-indian-passport-and-visa-centres-as-alhind-takes-over-consular-services/articleshow/131195661.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-19T14:51:41+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131195834,imgsize-111906.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ebola outbreak worries WHO over 'scale and speed': What to know]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131195981.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A severe Ebola outbreak, caused by the rare Bundibugyo virus, has claimed 130 lives with over 500 suspected cases.  The World Health Organization warns of high risk to neighboring nations, stressing human-to-human transmission via bodily fluids and contact with infected animals.  Emergency response systems are being activated to combat the escalating crisis.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/ebola-outbreak-worries-who-over-scale-and-speed-what-to-know/articleshow/131195981.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/ebola-outbreak-worries-who-over-scale-and-speed-what-to-know/articleshow/131195981.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-19T14:45:43+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131196019,imgsize-132470.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘They kicked me like an animal’: Israeli tourist speaking Hebrew attacked in London]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131195505.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/they-kicked-me-like-an-animal-jewish-tourist-from-israel-attacked-by-gang-in-londons-golders-green/articleshow/131195505.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/they-kicked-me-like-an-animal-jewish-tourist-from-israel-attacked-by-gang-in-londons-golders-green/articleshow/131195505.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-19T14:17:59+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131195605,imgsize-131258.cms"/></item></channel></rss>